MADRID. Cristiano Ronaldo is reportedly angry with his Real Madrid team-mates. The Portugal international has been on fire again this season under Zinedine Zidane. He has netted 22 goals and chipped in with 11 assists in all competitions. However, according to Spanish transfer outlet Don Balon, Ronaldo is unhappy and Lionel Messi is involved. The Real talisman feels that Barcelona build their team around Messi and the squad plays for the Argentina international.Ronaldo wants Real stars Karim Benzema and Gareth Bale to give him the same treatment as his rival gets from Neymar and Luis Suarez.The 32-year-old feels Benzema goes for goal too often while Bale is enthralled in the battle to be No.1 at the Bernabeu.Meanwhile, Alvaro Morata scored twice as Real Madrid maintained a two-point lead over Barcelona at the top of La Liga by making light of Ronaldo and Bale s absence in a 4-2 win at Leganes. Daily Star/AFP.